Ranger Help for: forage
=======================

SYNTAX:      forage
USAGE:       Any terrain
SLOT COST:   NA
BASE SP:     variable

SUMMARY:
This skill allows a Ranger to search the surrounding wilderness for
wildcraft supplies instead of loose inventory junk. What the Ranger
finds depends heavily on terrain. Forests and jungles are good for
binding fiber, resin, kindling, medicinal scraps, and tannin bark.
Wet terrain is better for clean water, and plains can provide
smokeleaf and useful fiber.

Use 'forage stores' to review your wildcraft pouch. If the pouch fills
with materials you do not need, use 'forage discard <component> [amount]'
to make room. For example, 'forage discard kindling 2' throws away two
kindling, and 'forage discard all confirm' empties the pouch.

These supplies feed Ranger survival skills such as mix, make tools,
make satchel, make fish trap, camp stock, camp cook, and camp brew.
